userComment.stringValue: Was great, thank you! It seems to have really helped. Because it was a very long flight I slept through one or two points and wasn’t sure when I woke up whether to go back and make up the ones I missed or not. Consider adding instruction on this!

On a long flight like NY to Auckland you tend to sleep for longer periods. This makes it difficult to use the app and apply the pressure points in a timely manner. Is there a way to do more pressure points before and after the flight rather than during the flight?  Both John and I recovered well from the flight. I was able to do the whole set ( didn’t sleep so well). John missed a few but still coped well with the jet lag.
There was a layover that reset the time. Rather than showing my body time from my actual departure airport it showed the stopover time that was not relevant to me.

userComment.stringValue: I was sleeping through a few of the pressure point tasks. I’m not sure how much of an effect that had on the result. I have found jet lag to be bad when traveling westbound from Europe to the United States. Not so much on the eastbound it does seem that my jet lag on this trip is not as bad as it has been in the past. It’s been two full days and I’m mostly adjusted to the timeframe. From what I remember, it would take me almost a week.

Great app - I believe activating these points reduced my jet lag by at least 50 percent. My only issue was - reaching the points on my feet is not always easy when flying, especially if I am seated in economy class.
